React
React is a open source javascript library which is used to build
single page application

react features
1) virtual dom- a copy of real dom - which compares changes by 
diffing algorithm and update the part of the content and the
entire process is called reconcialiation
2) component based architecture
3) single page application

component- a reusable part of UI 
two types
1) functional components - hooks
2) class components- life cycle methods


props
props are read only inputs which is used to pass the data to the child
it is an object



react rerenders only when the state changes
state -
it is like a variable used to store the data or manage the
dynamic nature of a component

hooks
hooks built in function used to perform react implementations

1) useState hook
it is used to manage the state
import {useState} from 'react'

const [count,setCount]=useState(0)
count---it is a state name
setCount----it is a function used to change the state value
        setCount('newvalue')
useState(0)-
hook(initialvalue)

2) useEffect
useEffect is a hook that is used to manage sideeeffects like
api calling, settimeout,setinterval and localstorage in a component

import {useEffect} from 'react'


1) useEffect with no dependencies - it will run everytime
useEffect(()=>{
        console.log('api calling')
})
above return

2) useEffect with empty dependency array- it will only one time
useEffect(()=>{
        console.log('api calling')
},[])

3) useEffect with dependecny array- it will run one time first time
and run again only when dependency value changes
useEffect(()=>{
        console.log('api calling')
},[apicount])



map
it is used for rendering a list
it is used to render the ui elements

key
it is used to provide unique identity for every rendered UI element


react router dom
it is used for navigation to multiple components
it is used for routing

browseerrouter---routes---route 

useNavigate()
it is react router dom hook that is used for programmatical routing

payemnt-------after few seconds----orderplaced


useParams()
it is used to get the dynamic data from the url